Derrick Spies, Correspondent The swimming pool in which a 5-year-old drowned. (Crisis Medical) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A five-year-old boy drowned at a residence in Melrose Avenue in Durban on Saturday. Crisis Medical spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, said emergency services arrived at the home shortly before 13:00 to find the young boy in a state of cardiac arrest. He said reports indicated that the child had been found unresponsive in the swimming pool. "Several advanced life support interventions were administered as paramedics tried fervently for over an hour in an attempt to resuscitate the child, however the attempts were unsuccessful," he said. Van Reenen said it was understood that the child accompanied his dad to work at the premises for the day. The scene was secured and handed over to the South African Police Services for further investigation and processing. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  